                            <comment id="16800489" author="alexott" created="Mon, 25 Mar 2019 08:51:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another, short term alternative is to use patched version of commons-configuration provided by RedHat: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/commons-configuration/commons-configuration/1.10.0.redhat-1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/commons-configuration/commons-configuration/1.10.0.redhat-1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16806771" author="spmallette" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2019 13:52:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the suggestion on the redhat version. that might be the best option for now as going to commons2 would be a breaking change in our release lines for the older versions we are supporting. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16806854" author="alexott" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2019 14:39:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I did try to make changes to support configuration2 - but it&apos;s a lot of changes, and I&apos;m not so deep into code to make sure that I won&apos;t break something&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
