                            <comment id="16809759" author="alexott" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2019 11:42:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;client referred to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONFIGURATION-581&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONFIGURATION-581&lt;/a&gt; that is duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONFIGURATION-540&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CONFIGURATION-540&lt;/a&gt; that could affect system properties&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16809777" author="rdale" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2019 12:05:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=alexott&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;alexott&quot;&gt;alexott&lt;/a&gt; Neither one is listed as a vulnerability.  So I don&apos;t see any need to update to the redhat version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16812445" author="spmallette" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2019 13:54:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tagged this for resolution in 3.5.0 when we can allow for a major breaking change in the API. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
